lied measures to investigate and amend shortcomings in the cpi methodology with the assistance of the oecd while estimates by the central bank would suggest that effects over the past price level trajectory were small with no consequences over the monetary policy likewise the international monetary fund noted that there is a downward bias in at least one component of the consumer price index but this bias does not seem to materially change the inflation picture in a public information notice released in july  moreover the associated report stated that “chile has a long record of highquality statistics and data are adequate for surveillance regarding the census assessments have exhibited mixed results an initial evaluation by a domestic independent experts panel released in august  placed the omission rate in  three times as much as other census in the region and recommended annulling the census to hold a new version in  the government sought an assessment by international experts before making a final decision the team which included three experts that represented the world bank and the eu statistics commission found “no basis for doubting the usability of the census data for most if perhaps not all of the customary uses and recommended its release subject to the elimination of the imputation of housing units not observed on the ground during the enumeration and the concurrent publication of a methodological and administrative report statisticsedit gdp compositionedit main macroeconomic aggregates of gdp aggregate  millions of clp   change yearonyear  private consumption    government consumption    changes in inventories   — gross fixed capital formation    exports    imports    exports minus imports   — gdp    note data are preliminary source cuentas nacionales de chile – evolución de la actividad económica en el año  p  central bank of chile accessed on  march  gdp by sectoredit gross domestic product by sector of the economy sector  millions of clp  agriculture 